<br>
 Dlaren <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushaihuludmohame.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaihulud Mohame</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/02 1:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Diety Effect</span><hr size=1> A truly intriguing discussion.  A look at the *recent* changes made to the crafting system, and the upcoming deity-focused Planes of Power expansion that the designers have shown an interest in allowing race and religion to play a more important role in Norrath.  I think that we can discuss this topic with &quot;realistic&quot; expectations of seeing some related changes in the future.  Assuming there are no drastic changes made to the spell system with PoP, and I believe there is little chance, implementation remains a problem.  I have to disagree with some of you in that I believe there <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> is</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a way for this concept to be implemented in today’s EQ, in a way.  The idea of deity imparting a corresponding bonus to a particular class of damage (i.e. Solusek Ro wizards receiving a bonus to fire-based damage) from character-creation is probably the most elegant solution.  Unfortunately, I do not believe that the mechanics required to implement this exist in the current game, nor do I believe that they ever will.  Changes of this nature, from a programming standpoint, would entail a re-work far too extensive.  However, as I mentioned earlier, the recent changes to player-made items could allow for a similar effect.  I can envision quests for each deity which reward an item, such as a ring, that would add bonuses and resists corresponding with that deity’s trademark magic type.  I think this is probably more feasible than innate bonuses.  Ideally, the quests would start at each deity’s temple and work in a way similar to that of the Qeynos badge quests.  Secondly, adding deity-specific spells of any kind, while interesting, would require a rather precarious balancing act.  As you can imagine, each deity’s spells would have to be similar to all the other deities’, so as to not overpower one, and would result in a rather bland assortment of similar spells of different types.  While essentially yielding the same results, this may, or may not, be easier to actually implement.  Again, I firmly believe that these benefits should be available from level 1-65.  Weather they are quest-able or available for purchase is irrelevant, but they should <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be dropped.<br>
     Regardless of how changes of this kind would be implemented, extreme mob resists could present a problem.  Any implementation of this kind would unavoidably make certain wizards more effective at certain types of magic (that is the idea after all right?).  If there existed a majority of mobs with a particular type of resistance, wizards of other specialties would be left at a disadvantage in those encounters.  Of course the severity of that disadvantage would depend entirely on how much more powerful deity-specific spells wound up being.<br>
<br>
~Shai<br>
Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utzeendao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzeen Dao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/02 5:49 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Diety Effect</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure the dev team made a comment at a recent Fan Faire saying they wished they had never put in diety restricted items. Turns out to be a much bigger pain than it's worth, in their eyes.<br>
<br>
I like the idea very much however. I'd rather there were specific spells instead of a &quot;behind the scenes&quot; modifier. More obvious and I like obvious.<br>
<br>
Instead of DDs, how about lines of the following:<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro: Self-only fire-based damage shield.<br>
<br>
Karana:Outdoor (they've moved away from this as well) pillar AE that's about 5% more mana efficient than current.<br>
<br>
Quellious: I like the concussion idea. Perfect.<br>
<br>
Inny: Hmmm, not sure.<br>
<br>
What other gods can wizards worship?<br>
<br>
pax,<br>
-Xoxxala<br>
